{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EGAUwS29ryUt9JCU2YRsrE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Diagnosis & Fix Summary\n\n### Root Cause\n\n**Data skew on `user_id=999`** causes Stage 3 OOM:\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Total records | 100,000 |\n| Distinct user_ids | 1,000 |\n| Hot key (`user_id=999`) records | 50,000 (50% of all data) |\n| Skew ratio | **500x** (threshold is 10x) |\n\nWhen Stage 3 runs `GROUP BY user_id`, the entire 50% of the dataset lands on a single executor partition (the one holding `user_id=999`). With only 256MB executor memory, that partition overflows → `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n### Fix Applied (Option B+C combined)\n\nThe `etl-job.yaml` was patched with two changes:\n\n1. **Increased executor memory** from `256m` → `1g`\n   ```\n   --conf spark.executor.memory=1g\n   ```\n\n2. **Enabled AQE with skew join handling** — Spark automatically splits the oversized `user_id=999` partition into sub-partitions:\n   ```\n   --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n   --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n   ```\n\n### Result\n\nThe ETL job completed successfully (`1/1`, 50s duration) and printed `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`. All three stages ran without OOM errors."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":214,"cache_read_input_tokens":41228,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":214},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2a0f63d7-0c2a-4ec4-b6fc-eadaef392896","uuid":"48d3b741-0aed-47ce-80c5-9a08d1822eaa","request_id":"req_011Cc4sXoyPJuuxv4LDxrAcF"}
